"n.任期；终身职位 【英】 n.任期，终身职位(th e right of holding something) 【记】 ten(拿住)+ure→任期 【例】 He will be given tenure at Columbia University this year. n. 终身职位; 占有期(占有不动产、土地或职位的期限) 【记】ten拿, ure－拿住职位的期限－任期 【记】同源于tain，拥有，指拥有某物如不动产或职位；音：特牛人，忒牛人，特牛的人，考GRE特牛的人就是以后变成终身教授；ten + year 十年，干了十年，终于获得终身教授的职位了； 【相关】attain 得到 获得，maintain 维持，维修，obtain 得到， tenure (n.)  early 15c., ""holding of a tenement,"" from Anglo-French and Old French tenure ""a tenure, estate in land"" (13c.), from Old French tenir ""to hold,"" from Vulgar Latin *tenire, from Latin tenere ""to hold"" (see tenet). The sense of ""condition or fact of holding a status, position, or occupation"" is first attested 1590s. Meaning ""guaranteed tenure of office"" (usually at a university or school) is recorded from 1957. Related: Tenured (1961)."
